Interesting, the issue seems to be coming from gvproxy. I wonder if it's macos that's restricting binding on a restricted port and not the linux vm as your certainly running rootful!

```
func annotateGvproxyResponseError(r io.Reader) error {
	b, err := io.ReadAll(r)
	if err == nil && len(b) > 0 {
		return fmt.Errorf("something went wrong with the request: %q", string(b))
	}
	return errors.New("something went wrong with the request, could not read response")
}
```

